        ],
        {
          "s": "), there may not be an obvious way to remove it."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Scope:"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " Verify existing insertion gap mechanism and keyboard shortcuts handle this. If not: clicking a non-editable block selects it (visual highlight), then Delete/Backspace removes it."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Effort:"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " Small. May already partially work via existing block management."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Update (implemented):"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " Block management is now complete. Non-editable blocks (hr, code blocks, eval blocks) get keyboard shortcuts: Backspace/Delete removes them, Enter inserts a paragraph after. Insertion gaps appear between adjacent non-editable blocks on hover, allowing paragraph insertion. Arrow keys navigate into/out-of non-editable blocks."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Tier 2: Architectural Unification"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "What makes Active Text notes "
        },
        [
          ":em",
          {
            "s": "better"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ", not just equal."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "4. Inline expression evaluation"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Gap:"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": ":field-ref"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " and "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": ":transclusion"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " are hardcoded renderer special cases. The "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "c0c0c0c0-005d-0000-0000-000000000000"
          },
          {
            "s": "Inline Expression Evaluation"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " proposal says they should be standard Hob "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "get-field"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " calls — the renderer should dispatch any non-keyword inline node to the evaluator, just as it already does at block level."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Why now:"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " This is the single change that unifies the inline story. Once inline expressions work:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": ":transclusion"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " → "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "(get-field @item-id :description)"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — no special-casing"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": ":field-ref"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " → "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "(get-field :self :field-name)"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — no special-casing"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Any Hob expression works inline — "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "(if condition \"yes\" \"no\")"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": ", user-defined macros, etc."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "The "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "@@"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " and "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "{{"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " autocomplete just insert different expression shapes"
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Scope:"
          }
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":ol",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Add evaluator fallback to "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "renderInlineNode"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " (matching what "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "renderNode"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " already does for blocks)"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Update "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "@@"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " autocomplete to insert "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "[\"get-field\", \"@item-id\", \":field\"]"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " instead of "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "[:transclusion, ...]"
              }
            ]
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
