          ":code",
          {
            "s": ">>>"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " shortcut creates a block-level eval block, which cannot nest inside a table cell. There is currently no way to insert executable Hob code inline within a table cell. Unlike headings, separators, and blockquotes (which are structural and correctly excluded from cells), eval expressions are "
        },
        [
          ":em",
          {
            "s": "content"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " — computed values, formulas, and dynamic lookups are all useful within table cells."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Scope:"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " Add an inline eval node type (or reuse the "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": ">>>"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " trigger in table cell context) that inserts an inline eval chip — similar to a field-ref pill but evaluating an arbitrary Hob expression. This is closely related to #4 (inline expression evaluation)."
        }
